<HL>
   Allwaste Sale of Guzzler Unit
</HL>
<DATE>
09/12/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4
</SO>
<CO>
   ALWS
</CO>
<IN>
POLLUTION CONTROL, WASTE MANAGEMENT SERVICES (POL)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   HOUSTON -- Allwaste Inc. said it completed the sale of its
Guzzler Manufacturing Inc. unit to Powerscreen International
PLC of the U.K., for about $18 million.
   The sale of Guzzler will result in a gain of $3.2 million
to $3.5 million, or nine cents to 10 cents a share, in the
fiscal first quarter ending Nov. 30.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In the year-earlier quarter, the company had net income of
$4.5 million, or 13 cents a share, on revenue of $57.3
million. Proceeds of the sale will be used to expand the
company's service businesses.
</TEXT>
